Never did I ever think I could replace balusters and install carpet and I’ve been an avid DIYer for over 10 years!

Every home renovation I’ve done has taught me not only new DIY skills but perseverance, courage and expanded my passion for creating your dream home no matter what phase of life you’re in!

In an effort to document more of my projects on my feed before we move and start this thing all over again, behold, my DIY staircase and foyer makeover! #mymonarchmanor

node.text:
Before last week I hadn’t paid much attention to our dining space. We converted our formal dining room into our music room so this space definitely gets a ton of use! I’ve spent the last week or so completely reimagining it to fit our family’s style!

The kitchen floors aren’t totally done but today my goal was to get the dining space pulled together and I got it done just in time to snap a couple of photos! #TheMonarchRevival

*Important* Several people asked me how I “know how” to do all these projects this week. I say I am self taught but as I took some time to think about it, I’m not. I’ve learned from reading tutorials, asking questions to my friends and family in construction, studying design every spare moment of my life, watching DIY on YouTube and Instagram, learning from other content creators that have become my friends and mentors. I learned right here with y’all watching. Trying and messing up but most importantly, never giving up.

node.text:
“I kinda think I should quit.” 

“What if I mess this up?”

“I should hire a pro to do this….”

No. 

This wallpaper was a challenge to install. Walls aren’t straight, square or plumb. There are 6 doors to go around and it’s really expensive paper. I had every excuse in the book to give up this week and truth be told, I’m not even done! (I need another roll!) 

BUT I FREAKING DID IT. I pushed myself through classic Mallory procrastination and fear and did the dang thing and I’m in love. Even Craiggy and my kids keep commenting on how nice it looks. #themonarchrevival

Whatever you do, whatever season you’re in, “don’t you give up. Don’t you quit. You keep trying. There is help and happiness ahead.” -Jeffrey R. Holland

Oh! Swipe to see the foyer view before/after and my new favorite pic of Ollie and I. ✨

This is 35! 🎉🎂

It feels a lot older than 34 but I’m determined to make it the best year yet!

I thought it’d be fun to share a few random things about me!

•I’m the oldest of 5 siblings! 
•I have 5 boys and no we weren’t “trying for a girl” 😂
•I drove a cop car in high school. 
•I’m blind in my right eye. 
•Buzz feed posted a picture of me and Taylor Swift in front of her NYC home!
•I once did a back handspring on the Hoover Dam!
•I’ve been married for 15 years and moved 13 times!
•I love sushi, sour candy, Dr Pepper, FRIENDS, Taylor Swift and NYC! 
•I’ve been doing DIY and blogging for 11 years (way before Instagram was a thing!)

Tell me one unique thing about you! Any July birthday buddies?

node.text:
Coco Chanel said “An interior is the natural projection of the soul.” That struck a chord with me. Our homes should reflect who we are, what we like and “feel” like the people who live there. #themonarchrevival

This room feels like me. 

It’s a collection of some of my favorite pieces, colors and textures. Traditional yet modern, classic, bold and feminine. In a home of 6 boys, I wanted an elegant sitting room to cozy up next to my husband and read a… errr scroll Instagram. 😉

I’d love to hear, what’s your design style?

From the hills of Tennessee, God bless the USA! 🇺🇸

 #themonarchrevival

In just 24 hours we recreated our favorite Harry Potter bedroom (2.0) as a last ditch effort to get our home ready for guests!

We still have a starry night ceiling and floating candles to add but we are obsessed! Now I’m itching to create a Harry Potter inspired retreat in the attached bathroom!  #mymonarchrevival

In a few hours of pretty easy and really fun DIY projects I completely transformed our powder room just in time for guests to come visit! It’s truly remarkable what paint and accessories can do!

Don’t be afraid to go bold in small spaces! The black walls make the space feel cozy and glamorous and actually draws your eye UP to the 10’ ceilings that went unnoticed before! #themonarchrevival

My goal was dramatic and glamorous and I love how it turned out! I also lucked out having almost all my supplies and decor on hand!

🖤 Would you ever paint your walls black? 🖤

Color: @behrpaint Carbon
Art: @bffprintshop

node.text: Our foyer renovation is in full swing! As I’ve been working in here almost every day, I was able to take a closer look at just how often we actually use our staircase with my @microban24 24-Hour Bacteria Cam. #Microban24Partner The handrails are touched way more than I thought in a 24 hour period!! We have second staircase that gets just as much use. Luckily, I can spray Microban 24 on our handrails and other high-touch surfaces to keep killing bacteria for 24 hours even after all those touches! Especially after school pick up! 😆 With a family of 7, we're always running around and going up and down the stairs, so by sanitizing, I'm the MVP (most valuable protector)! #Microban24MVP Also, can you believe how different our foyer looks already! Loving this new tile SO much! #themonarchrevival

3 years ago today, my little sister Brittany passed away unexpectedly. She was 30. She left behind 2 beautiful daughters that I love and cherish like my own. I never had a daughter so these girls are as close to me as my own.

Brittany and I married brothers in 2006 and although they were no longer married when she passed, my sister and I share maiden and married names. We call our kiddos double cousins. They are as close as they come!

When she left us for her Heavenly home, her girls and I decided that whenever we see a butterfly, Brittany was near. I couldn’t bear the thought of her not being near so I sprinkled my home with butterflies so I could never go a day without thinking about her. Today, I created my butterfly wall in honor of her 3 years in Heaven! It’s my favorite way to keep her memory alive. I miss you, sister. Love you forever Britter! #theMonarchRevival
